    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryDef_2">Definitions:\n
◦ Error = difference between exact (x) and approximate (a) value.\n
◦ Absolute Error: Δ = |x - a|, distance between x and a.\n
◦ Bound of Absolute Error: |x - a| ≤ h → x = a ± h.\n
◦ Relative Error: δ = Δ / |a|, often given as a percentage.\n
◦ Bound of Relative Error: ε = h / |a| → x = a(1 ± ε).</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryDefQuestion_2">An exact value is 7.3 and its approximation is 7. What is the absolute error Δ?</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryDefAnswerOne_2">0.3</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryDefAnswerTwo_2">0.7</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryDefAnswerThree_2">1</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryDefCorrectAnswer_2">0.3</string>

    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryProperties_2">Properties:\n
◦ The absolute error is always non-negative: Δ ≥ 0.\n
◦ The relative error is dimensionless and independent of units.\n
◦ A smaller relative error means a more accurate approximation.\n
◦ When h is known, the exact value lies in the interval [a − h, a + h].\n
◦ The relative error grows large when the approximate value |a| is close to zero.</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryPropsQuestion_2">An approximation is a = 50 with h = 1. What is the bound of relative error ε?</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryPropsAnswerOne_2">0.05</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryPropsAnswerTwo_2">0.02</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryPropsAnswerThree_2">0.5</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryPropsCorrectAnswer_2">0.02</string>

    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryWorkedExamples_2">A value is approximated as a = 3.14 with h = 0.005.\n
Step 1: Absolute error bound: |x − 3.14| ≤ 0.005.\n
Step 2: Relative error bound: ε = 0.005 / 3.14 ≈ 0.0016 ≈ 0.16%.\n
Step 3: So x = 3.14(1 ± 0.0016).</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryWorkedExQuestion_2">With a = 3.14 and h = 0.005, what is the bound of relative error ε (rounded to 4 decimal places)?</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryWorkedExAnswerOne_2">0.0050</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryWorkedExAnswerTwo_2">0.0314</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryWorkedExAnswerThree_2">0.0016</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryWorkedExCorrectAnswer_2">0.0016</string>

