    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryDef_2">Definitions:\n
• Bound of Absolute Error (Product): h_ab ≈ ah_b + bh_a.\n
• Bound of Relative Error (Product/Quotient): ε_ab ≈ ε_a + ε_b, ε_(a/b) = ε_a + ε_b.\n
• Relative error is often found first, then absolute error.</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryDefQuestion_2">If ε_a = 0.01 and ε_b = 0.02, what is the bound of relative error of a · b?</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryDefAnswerOne_2">0.01</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryDefAnswerTwo_2">0.02</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryDefAnswerThree_2">0.03</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryDefCorrectAnswer_2">0.03</string>

    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryProperties_2">Properties:\n
Practical Rule for Multiply/Divide:\n
1. Identify least accurate factor.\n
2. Round others to one more significant digit.\n
3. Compute normally.\n
4. Round result to match least accurate factor.</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryPropsQuestion_2">Is the bound of relative error of a/b equal to ε_a + ε_b? (True / False)</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryPropsAnswerOne_2">True</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryPropsAnswerTwo_2">False</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryPropsAnswerThree_2">Neither</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryPropsCorrectAnswer_2">True</string>

    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryWorkedExamples_2">Multiply a = 3.2 (h_a = 0.05) by b = 5.0 (h_b = 0.05).\n
Step 1: Product: 3.2 × 5.0 = 16.0.\n
Step 2: ε_a = 0.05/3.2 ≈ 0.0156; ε_b = 0.05/5.0 = 0.01.\n
Step 3: ε_ab ≈ 0.0156 + 0.01 = 0.0256.\n
Step 4: h_ab = ε_ab × |ab| = 0.0256 × 16.0 ≈ 0.41.</string>
    <string name="SectionFiveTheoryWorkedExQuestion_2">With a = 3.2, b = 5.0, and ε_ab ≈ 0.0256, what is the bound of absolute error of the product (rounded to 2 decimal places)?</string>
